#: src/pages/docs/DevicesHelpPage.tsx:33
msgid "A managed device is a piece of hardware Multiview supervises: a hardware decoder feeding a TV, a display node driving a video wall, or a cast target. The device entry you adopt is desired state — driver, management address, mode, credentials — and a supervised driver continuously converges the real device onto it: it probes, reconnects, re-applies the mode, and reports status."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/DevicesPage.tsx:669
msgid "A managed device is declarative desired state: adopting starts a supervised driver that probes and converges it."
msgstr ""

#: src/resources/FormControls.tsx:72
msgid "A mount point must start with /, e.g. /multiview."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ConfigPage.tsx:26
msgid "A Multiview deployment is one declarative document. It is authored as TOML and round-trips losslessly to JSON (the API wire form)."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/concepts/CodecsPage.tsx:40
msgid "A multiviewer is inherently a transcoder: it must decode every source to composite them into one canvas, and then encode that canvas for its outputs. What it never does is transcode each tile separately — the cost would multiply by the number of tiles for no benefit."
msgstr ""

