#: src/pages/docs/concepts/LatencyPage.tsx:28
msgid "Glass-to-glass latency is the time from light hitting a camera sensor (\"first glass\") to the picture appearing on a display (\"second glass\"). It is a chain of small budgets, and every hop adds some: the camera's own encoder, the network transport, any receive/jitter buffering, decoding, compositing, re-encoding the canvas, the output transport, and finally the viewer's player buffer. No single component \"is\" the latency — the chain is."
msgstr ""

#: src/docs/registry.ts:594
