#: src/pages/docs/concepts/TransportsPage.tsx:199
msgid "WebRTC carries sub-second video and audio straight to and from a browser with no plugin. Multiview speaks the two open HTTP signalling profiles built on it: <0>WHIP</0> (WebRTC-HTTP Ingestion Protocol) for a browser or encoder to publish a feed into a <1>webrtc</1> source, and <2>WHEP</2> (WebRTC-HTTP Egress Protocol) for a browser to play a <3>webrtc</3> output or a live preview. Both negotiate once over HTTPS — the client POSTs an SDP offer and gets the answer back — then media flows directly over the negotiated peer connection."
msgstr ""

